<div id="review_2679155142" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2679155142" />
    <a title="Jacob Rundle" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/87844985-jacob-rundle"><img alt="Jacob Rundle" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1594737816p2/87844985.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2679155142?book_show_action=true">Jan 18, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jacob Rundle" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jacob Rundle" href="/user/show/87844985-jacob-rundle">Jacob Rundle</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2679155142" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer484436925193381892">The Sound of Suffering gets a 4.5/5.0. The characters were realistic and relatable. I enjoyed the story. I believed that the aura manipulation was interesting. The character development was well done. The pacing was good, and I didn&apos;t see any plot holes. The world-building was new and refreshing. Overall, I really enjoyed this novel.</span>
  <span id="freeText484436925193381892" style="display:none">The Sound of Suffering gets a 4.5/5.0. The characters were realistic and relatable. I enjoyed the story. I believed that the aura manipulation was interesting. The character development was well done. The pacing was good, and I didn't see any plot holes. The world-building was new and refreshing. Overall, I really enjoyed this novel.</span>
